Note: English names for countries or territories are in parentheses.
Special Forces.
The legion does not have any official special operations units, and has no units within the 1st circle of Special Operations Command, but it has elite pathfinding, Amphibious EOD and recon units that operate, train and function like most Special operations units – Commando Parachute Group, Mountain Commando group and DINOPS (now named PCG).
There is at-least one GCP (Commando Parachute Group) team within every regiment of 11th Parachute Brigade (2REP is part of this), GCP teams usually do PathFinding and long range reconnaissance for the unit they originated from.
